reviews.text: Scored 3.7 stars. Came across eating halfcooked spareribs that made me feel I were a flesh-eating barbarian at the moment... Fluctuated cooking quality.

Is my expectation too big? Whenever I come here, I have to leave disappointed. Ok, it is one kind of Hong Kong style fast food shop, nothing is more than this. It insists that it is the biggest noodle and congee chainshop in Hong Kong. But I wonder How?

Congee is acceptable, while noodle and rice menu are below than average of similar style fast food shop. Tables and floor are not so clean. Staffs are serving in average manner. I think it has a lot of potentiality to improve.
